Span.End() adds slog.String("component", "perf") as a caller-provided attr while logging.Debug also extracts component from the context. This will emit duplicate component keys in the JSON log line (e.g., one from context like "hooks" plus "perf"), which can confuse log ingestion/parsing. Consider setting the component via context (e.g., logging.WithComponent(s.ctx, "perf")) and not emitting a separate component attribute, or otherwise ensure only one component key is logged.